==English==
===Verbal phrase===
''to'' '''hang in there'''

# To [[subsist]] while keeping high [[spirits]].
# To [[maintain]] a [[course]] of [[action]] despite [[negative]] [[outlook]].

====Usage notes====
Used mainly in the imperative.

====Antonyms====
* (''maintain a course of action''): [[back out]], [[give up]], [[withdraw]]

===Interjection===
'''Hang in there!'''

# [[Brace]] yourself.